data.name: Savory Beef & Broccoli Stir-Fry
data.quickTastyDescription: A quick and nutritious stir-fry featuring tender ground beef and fresh broccoli in a savory sauce.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large skillet, heat the sesame oil over medium-high heat.
Add the minced garlic and ginger, saut√© for 1 minute until fragrant.
Add the ground beef to the skillet, breaking it apart with a spatula. Cook until browned and fully cooked, about 5-7 minutes.
Add the broccoli florets to the skillet and stir-fry for another 3-4 minutes until they are bright green and tender-crisp.

In a small bowl, mix the soy sauce, water, cornstarch, salt, and pepper. Pour this mixture over the beef and broccoli. Stir well to combine and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes until the sauce thickens.
Serve hot, garnished with sliced green onions and sesame seeds.
data.modifiersForBase: Stir-fried with Broccoli and a Soy-Ginger Sauce
